CatDescriptText: Mr. Ulric Downes, musician, 8 Miller St., was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 19, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that cab drivers in general take advantage of other motorists and pedestrians in traffic? As a group, would you call them courteous or discourteous?" answer reads: "At times, a few do.  And as for discourtesy, at times, a few also do not heed the feeling of others."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Ulric Downes wearing button down plaid collared shirt and cap, standing in front of chain link fence with manufacturing buildings in background
